#Approach:

Roman to Integer – Left to Right Comparison Approach

Roman numerals me normally bada symbol pehle aata hai aur chhota baad me,
to hum value add karte hain.
Lekin agar chhota symbol bade symbol se pehle aa jaye,
to us case me subtract karna padta hai (jaise IV = 4, IX = 9).

Isliye hum string ko left se right traverse karte hain
aur current character ko next character se compare karte hain.

Agar current value < next value,
to iska matlab subtraction case hai,
to current value ko answer me subtract kar dete hain.

Agar current value >= next value,
to normal case hai,
to current value ko answer me add kar dete hain.

Is tarah poori string traverse karne ke baad final integer mil jata hai.

Example:
MCMXCIV
M = +1000
C < M → -100
M = +1000
X < C → -10
C = +100
I < V → -1
V = +5

Total = 1994

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int romanToInt(String s) {
        HashMap<Character, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

        map.put('V', 5);
        map.put('I', 1);
        map.put('X', 10);
        map.put('L', 50);
        map.put('C', 100);
        map.put('D', 500);
        map.put('M', 1000);

        int ans = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++){
            if(i+1 < s.length() && map.get(s.charAt(i)) < map.get(s.charAt(i+1))){
                ans -= map.get(s.charAt(i));
            }
            else{
                ans += map.get(s.charAt(i));
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
